HEADWORD: Mucor
<hw>Mu"cor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>mucere</ets> to be moldy or musty.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of minute fungi. The plants consist of slender threads with
terminal globular sporangia; mold.</def>⟦br⟧
